      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The funds are held by a neutral third party, usually a title company or an escrow agent, who is legally obligated to manage the account. This agent oversees the release of funds according to the purchase contract's specific terms. They act as a fiduciary, meaning they must handle the money strictly according to the agreement, keeping it safe from either the buyer or the seller until the closing occurs.",
